sequenceDiagram
    actor Host as Host (Client)
    participant HC as Host Controller
    participant HS as Host Service
    participant SimSvc as Simulator Service
    participant SS as Storage Service
    participant S3 as AWS S3
    participant DB as Prisma DB

    Note over Host,DB: PHASE 1: Create Simulator (without images)
    
    Host->>HC: POST /host/simulator<br/>(name, description, price, location, modid, types)
    
    HC->>HS: uploadSimulator(createSimulatorDto, hostId)
    Note over HS: Note: CreateSimulatorDto has NO image fields
    
    HS->>SimSvc: create(createSimulatorDto, hostId)
    
    SimSvc->>DB: prisma.simulator.create()
    Note over DB: Create base simulator with<br/>firstImage, secondImage, thirdImage = null
    
    SimSvc->>DB: simulatorTypeList.createMany()
    Note over DB: Link simulator types
    
    DB-->>SimSvc: {id: 123, ...}
    SimSvc-->>HS: {message: 'Upload Success', simid: 123}
    HS-->>Host: {message: 'Upload Success', simid: 123}
    
    Note over Host,DB: PHASE 2: Upload Images (separate flow)
    
    Host->>HC: POST /host/simulator/123/image-upload<br/>{contentType: 'image/jpeg'}
    
    HC->>HS: createSimulatorImageUpload(hostId, 123, contentType)
    
    HS->>DB: Verify simulator 123 exists & ownership
    HS->>SS: createPresignedUploadUrl()
    
    Note over SS: Generates S3 Key:<br/>simulators/sim/123/{timestamp}-{uuid}.jpg
    
    SS->>S3: Get signed PUT URL
    S3-->>SS: Pre-signed URL
    
    SS-->>HS: {uploadUrl, publicUrl, objectKey, expiresInSeconds}
    HS-->>Host: Return presigned data
    
    Host->>S3: PUT /uploadUrl (image file)
    S3-->>Host: 200 OK
    
    Note over Host,DB: PHASE 3: Confirm Image Upload
    
    Host->>HC: PATCH /host/simulator/123/images/confirm<br/>{firstImageKey: 'simulators/sim/123/...'}
    
    HC->>HS: confirmSimulatorImages(123, imageKeys, hostId)
    
    HS->>DB: Verify ownership
    
    HS->>SS: assertObjectExists(firstImageKey)
    Note over SS: Checks image exists in S3
    
    HS->>SimSvc: update(123, {firstImageKey}, hostId)
    
    Note over SimSvc: updateMapping() converts<br/>S3 key to CDN URL
    
    SimSvc->>DB: simulator.update({firstImage: CDN_URL})
    
    DB-->>SimSvc: Updated simulator
    SimSvc-->>HS: Updated simulator
    HS-->>Host: Complete simulator with image URL